    "content": "<p>4\ufe0f\u20e36\ufe0f\u20e3 Here&#39;s the 46th post highlighting key new features of the upcoming v258 release of systemd. <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/systemd258\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>systemd258</span></a></p><p>The various ProtectXYZ= settings for service unit files allow locking services into sandboxes in a relatively fine grained fashion.</p><p>The ProtectHostname=yes option is one of these options: it locks the service into a &quot;uts&quot; namespace (which is a Linux kernel construct that disconnects the system hostname the service uses from the hostname the rest of the system sees).</p>",
