      "edited_at": null,
      "content": "<p>It also enforces some &quot;seccomp&quot; based restrictions on the system calls to change the hostname. Altogether it is a simple way to &quot;freeze&quot; the hostname for a specific service, and ensure it cannot alter it itself (it might still do so indirectly, if it has suitable access to an IPC service doing it for it, for example systemd-hostnamed, hence is only part of the puzzle to lock things down, it&#39;s not a one-stop solution blocking hostname changes altogether \u2013</p>",
