      "content": "<p>and this should not be misunderstood).</p><p>With v258 we are extending the setting in two ways: so far the option was a boolean. Now it takes a third value: &quot;private&quot;. If set to that, the hostname is disconnected as before, but hostname changes are not prohibited for the service \u2013 however they won&#39;t propagate to the system as a whole.</p><p>And there&#39;s one more trick the setting now has up its sleeve: you may now suffix the setting with a colon, followed by a literal hostname specification, \u2026</p>",
