      "edited_at": "2025-08-26T15:53:44.070Z",
      "content": "<p>\u2026 which has the effect of not only disconnecting the hostname from the host (and possibly prohibiting an attempts to change it), but also initializing it to some string of choice.</p><p>Example: ProtectHostname=private:foobar</p><p>This will disconnect the hostname from the rest of the system, and set the hostname from the service&#39;s PoV to &quot;foobar&quot;. The service may change the hostname via sethostname() during runtime, which will be in effect for that service, but nothing else on the system.</p>",
